  "prompt": "Did anybody ever document what the Dodo bird of Mauritius tasted like?",
  "response": "Historical accounts and anecdotal evidence suggest that the dodo bird, which was native to Mauritius, was not particularly palatable. Sailors and settlers who encountered the bird in the 16th and 17th centuries reported that its meat was tough and not very tasty. However, these accounts are largely second-hand stories, and no detailed documentation or culinary descriptions of the dodo's taste survive to provide definitive insights. The dodo was driven to extinction by the late 17th century due to hunting, habitat destruction, and the introduction of foreign animals that preyed on its eggs.",
